# Deobfuscated Code & Explanation

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;          // 2π
var PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // √(1/2)

// Simulation configuration
var config = {
    yield: 4000,           // Repulsion strength between nodes
    leverage: 0.004,       // Spring stiffness default
    volatility: 0.92,      // Velocity damping factor
    liquidity: 0.0003,     // Centering force strength
    portfolio: 40,         // Max number of particles
    correlation: 0.04,     // Particle friction
    delta: 0.06            // Camera smoothing factor
};

// Nodes (graph vertices)
var nodes = [
    { id: "hub",     label: "Hub",     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Edges (springs connecting nodes)
var edges = [
    { a: "hub",   b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particles array and frame counter
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Physics simulation step
function applyForces() {
    // 1. Node-to-node repulsion (inverse-square law)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.yield / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2. Spring forces along edges (Hooke's law)
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        var nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
        var nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
        var force = (edges[i].k || config.leverage) * displacement;
        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3. Apply velocity: damping, centering gravity, and position update
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.liquidity;  // center gravity X
        nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.liquidity;  // center gravity Y
        nodes[i].vx *= config.volatility;  // damping
        nodes[i].vy *= config.volatility;
        nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
        nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a new particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.portfolio) return;
    var node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;
    particles.push({
        x: node.x,
        y: node.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// Update all particles
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.correlation * 0.125;   // friction
        p.vy *= 1 - config.correlation * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);  // remove expired
    }
}

// Smooth camera towards target
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.delta;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.delta;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.delta;
}

// Main loop
function tick() {
    applyForces();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
    frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16);  // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** — a physics-based layout engine for visualizing a network of 6 nodes connected by 8 edges. Here's the breakdown:

### Core Mechanics

| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Repulsion** | All nodes repel each other with an inverse-square force (like charged particles), preventing overlap |
| **Springs** | Connected nodes are pulled together by spring forces (Hooke's law) with configurable rest lengths and stiffnesses |
| **Damping** | Velocities are multiplied by 0.92 each frame to prevent infinite oscillation |
| **Centering** | A weak gravity pulls all nodes toward the center point (400, 300) |
| **Particles** | Decorative particles spawn from random nodes, drift outward, and fade/die after a random lifespan |
| **Camera** | A smooth-following camera that interpolates toward a target position |

### The Graph Structure

```
        Epsilon
       /       \
    Hub ------- Alpha
   / |  \         |
Gamma |   \      Beta
   \  |    \    /
    Delta   (Alpha-Beta)
```

A **hub-and-spoke** topology where "Hub" is the central node connected to all others, with a few cross-links (Alpha↔Beta, Gamma↔Delta, Alpha↔Epsilon).

### Financial Theming
The config parameters use financial terms (`yield`, `leverage`, `volatility`, `liquidity`, `portfolio`, `correlation`, `delta`) as variable names — purely cosmetic obfuscation to make the code harder to understand. The Greek letter node names (Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon) reinforce this theme.

### Summary
**This is a headless (no rendering code) force-directed graph physics engine** that runs at ~60 FPS, continuously simulating node positions and spawning ambient particles. It would typically be paired with a Canvas/WebGL renderer to visualize the network.
